<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-05-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="806" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d806">
                        <head>806. Telegram 1193 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d806fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/5–1457.
                                Confidential; Priority. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName> and Henderson; cleared by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName> and
                            Jones.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-05-14">May 14, 1957, 5:55
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d806-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d806-1"/>
                        <p>1193. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Supplementary guidance regarding paragraph 3 Department’s telegram
                            1181.</p>
                        <p>Public policy on MATADOR deployment to Taiwan has been to emphasize
                            defensive nature of move and treat weapon on same basis as any other
                            piece standard US Air Force equipment. You should take same line,
                            emphasizing need for US defensive arrangements in Taiwan area, but
                            avoiding discussion of propriety this particular weapon if <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> should attempt draw you into
                            discussing this.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1"><hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>